Privacy Policy

Effective Date: July 11, 2026

Golden Fish Rush / Golden Fish Dash (“the App”) is a mobile game developed and published by Hasan Hussein (“we”, “our”, or “us”).

This Privacy Policy explains how information is collected, used, and protected when you use the App.

1. Information We Collect

The App does not require users to create an account.

The App may collect or store the following types of information:

a. Local Game Data

The App stores some gameplay progress locally on your device, such as:

- Best score
- Coins
- Unlocked fish skins
- Selected fish skin
- Shop items
- Daily rewards
- Game settings
- Achievements

This information is stored locally on your device and is used only to provide game features.

b. Leaderboard Data

If you choose to submit your score to the leaderboard, the App may collect:

- Player name entered by you
- Score
- Submission date/time

This data is stored using Firebase Firestore and may be displayed publicly in the leaderboard inside the App.

Please do not enter your real full name or any sensitive personal information as your leaderboard name.

c. Advertising Data

The App may display advertisements using third-party advertising services such as Google AdMob.

Advertising partners may collect certain information to provide and improve ads, such as:

- Device information
- Advertising identifiers
- App usage data
- Approximate location
- Ad interactions

These third-party services may use cookies, device identifiers, or similar technologies according to their own privacy policies.

d. Analytics and Crash Data

The App may use services such as Firebase or Google services to help improve performance, fix bugs, and understand general app usage.

This may include non-personal technical information such as:

- Device type
- Operating system version
- App version
- Crash reports
- General usage events

2. How We Use Information

We use collected or stored information to:

- Save game progress
- Display leaderboard scores
- Improve gameplay experience
- Provide rewards and shop features
- Show advertisements
- Improve app performance and stability
- Prevent abuse of leaderboard features

3. Third-Party Services

The App may use third-party services that collect information according to their own privacy policies.

These services may include:

- Firebase
- Google Play Services
- Google AdMob
- Google Analytics for Firebase

You can review Google’s Privacy Policy here:

https://policies.google.com/privacy

4. Leaderboard Visibility

If you submit a score, your chosen display name and score may be visible to other users of the App.

Do not submit any personal, private, or sensitive information as your leaderboard name.

5. Children’s Privacy

The App is intended for a general audience.

We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you believe that a child has provided personal information through the App, please contact us and we will take appropriate action.

6. Data Security

We take reasonable steps to protect information used by the App.

However, no method of electronic storage or transmission over the internet is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.

7. Your Choices

You can manage or delete local game data by:

- Clearing the App’s storage from your device settings
- Uninstalling the App

Leaderboard data submitted online may remain stored unless removed by us.

If you want your leaderboard entry removed, you may contact us.

8. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time.

Any changes will be posted on this page with an updated Effective Date.

